cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SE 

This paper discusses a protocol for secure function evaluation (SFE) using Intel's Software Guard Extensions (SGX), which provides hardware-protected execution environments. The paper focuses on the security aspects of the protocol and discusses the use of SGX as a trusted computation oracle. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the implementation of the protocol and its performance, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also applies the protocol to privacy-preserving queries to a database and a version of Dijkstra's algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
